The `DashboardLayout` component serves as the main structural layout for the application's dashboard section. It sets up a two-column layout, with a fixed sidebar on the left and the main content area that takes up the remaining space on the right.

## Purpose

- Provides a consistent layout for all pages within the `/dashboard` route.
- Integrates a `Sidebar` component for navigation.
- Manages the overall screen structure, ensuring responsiveness and scrollability for the main content.

## Key Exports

- `default` (React Component): The primary export, rendering the dashboard layout.

## Props

- `children` (React.ReactNode): The content that will be rendered within the main area of the dashboard. This allows for dynamic content from nested routes.

## Usage

This component is used in `app/dashboard/layout.tsx` to wrap all child routes within the `/dashboard` path. It's typically not used directly by other components, but rather by the framework's routing system.

```typescript
// app/dashboard/layout.tsx
import { Sidebar } from "@/components/ui/sidebar";

export default function DashboardLayout({
  children,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode;
}) {
  return (
    <div className="flex h-screen bg-background overflow-hidden">
      <Sidebar />
      <main className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto">{children}</main>
    </div>
  );
}
```
